        "title": "Bert de Groot",
        "excerpt":"  Affiliation   Max Planck Institute for Multidisciplinary Sciences, Goettingen, Germany     Alchemical binding free energy calculations for ligand binding, protein allostery, post-translational modifications, and more       Abstract   Alchemical free energy calculations have come of age. These calculations explore physical paths not experimentally accessible and provide unprecedented accuracy in the prediction of processes as diverse as protein thermostability and ligand binding free energies. Based on the PMX framework coupled to the GROMACS molecular dynamics engine, results of high-throughput relative as well as absolute ligand binding  free energies are presented, in addition to applications of allostery in a GPCR and the effect of post-translational modifications in protein aggregation.  ","categories": ["speakers","people"],
